<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 01 at 7:44PM CDT until September 01 at 8:15PM CDT by NWS Dodge City</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Dodge City has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Ford County in southwestern Kansas...
* Until 815 PM CDT.
* At 743 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Dodge City,
moving southwest at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southwestern Ford County.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
